Perfect — here’s a single PowerShell line that will:

Create a fresh dump of your va-disabilities database.

Save it to your Desktop.

Copy it to your Ubuntu server.

Import it there.

& "C:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 8.0\bin\mysqldump.exe" -u root -p va-disabilities | Out-File -Encoding UTF8 "C:\Users\gianu\OneDrive\Desktop\va-disabilities.sql"; scp "C:\Users\gianu\OneDrive\Desktop\va-disabilities.sql" root@67.205.168.90:/root/; ssh root@67.205.168.90 "mysql -u root -p va-disabilities < /root/va-disabilities.sql"

CHECK UBANTU RELEASE for upgrades in powershell
ssh root@67.205.168.90 

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo do-release-upgrade
